text.tspan: Across the oceans lies a land of incredible natural beauty and diversity.
Long-inhabited by the indigenous peoples of the region, Japanese
colonisation led to the formation of Chrysanthemum State. Our people
and culture, while having links with Japan and the Japonosphere, have
become distinct through our history on this land. From the great
Outback to temperate rainforests, from plains to metropolises, we are
proud to call Chrysanthemum State home.
